headline: Europe reluctant to confront the United States on tariffs
description: European leaders thrashed out a trade strategy with the United States at a summit in Brussels, ahead of a July 9 tariff deadline. Germany is pushing for a conciliatory approach, while France is calling for a firm hand.

description: Sensory tours at the Musée Rodin and Musée de l'Orangerie, mezzo forte concerts from the Orchestre Lamoureux, joyful splashing at Centquatre-Paris: More and more cultural venues in the French capital are offering activities for children under the age of two.

headline: 'Trump's attack on birthright citizenship serves to expand his authority by jeopardizing the status of all Americans'
description: By executive order, the fate of which hangs on a Supreme Court decision expected Friday, June 27, anyone living in the US could be required to prove their ancestry to pass their nationality on to their children. Such a scenario would give the administration greater control over the population, warns American law professor Amanda Frost.
